# FashionMNIST Classifier - CSC3022F ML-Assignment 1

## Project Overview
This repository contains an Artificial Neural Network (ANN) implementation for classifying FashionMNIST images into 10 fashion categories. The system includes model training, evaluation, and interactive image classification capabilities.

## File Structure

|---fashion-jpegs/
|---FashionMNIST/
|---src/
    |---classifier.py
    |---data_loading.py
|---.gitignore
|---log.txt
|---ReadME

## File Description

### 1. classifier.py
***Purpose**: Main executable script for the entire project
***Functionality***:
- Defines the neural network architecture
- contains the training loop with Adam optimizer
- Implements test set evaluation
- Provides user interactive image classification via command line
- Measures precise training times

**Usage**:
python3 src/classifier.py

2. data_loading.py
***Purpose***: Handles data related operations
***Functionality***:
- Loads FashionMNIST dataset
- Applies transformations (normalization, ToTensor)
- creates DataLoader instances for batch processing

3. fashion_classifier.pth
***Purpose***: Serialized model weights
***Generated When***:
- Automatically created after successful training
- Contains the state dict of the best performing model

4. log.txt
***Purpose***: Training process documentation
***Contains***: 
- Epoch loss values
- Final test accuracy
- Traing time

## Usage Example

1. Train Model:
python3 src/classifier.py

2. Classify an image:
> Please enter a filepath (or 'exit' to quit): fasion-jpegs/bag.jpg
Classifier: Bag